President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Robert W. Holleyman II as Deputy United States Trade Representative, Lisa S. Disbrow as Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Financial Management, Laura Junor as Principal Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness, and Karen Kornbluh as Member of the Broadcasting Board of Governors. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint individuals to key Administration posts, such as Leslie Meyers as Member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council and Janet Hill, Michael Lombardo, Rose Kennedy Schlossberg, Susan S. Sher, and John W. Rogers, Jr. as Trustees of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Additionally, President Obama announced the appointment of Joe Echevarria as Member of the Presidentâ€™s Export Council.